<HEADLINE> Argentine President Pays Visit to Colombia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTAFE DE BOGOTA, September 29 (Xinhua) -- Argentine President
Carlos Menem arrived in Colombia on Wednesday for an official
short visit.
</P>
<P>
Colombian President Andres Pastrana had invited Menem to hold a
"highest political dialogue" for strengthening the relations
between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Both heads of State will sign a joint declaration on the
bilateral relations.
</P>
<P>
Menem's visit to Colombia will last only a few hours, as he is
travelling to the United States in the afternoon, where he will
participate in the 8th Annual Conference of the Americas.
</P>
<P>
Menem's entourage include Defense Minister Jorge Dominguez and
Justice Minister Raul Granillo Ocampo. 
</P>
