<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Arab Groups to Campaign for Defense of Jerusalem </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, September 29 (Xinhua) -- Arab unions and
non-governmental organizations have agreed on a plan of action to
"confront Israeli plots on Jerusalem."
</P>
<P>
The Arab groups outlined the plan at a meeting Tuesday night,
Egypt's Middle East News Agency reported on Wednesday. The
execution of the plan will be overseen by the Arab Popular
Committee for the Defense of Jerusalem.
</P>
<P>
The African-Asian Peoples Solidarity Organization, the Arab
Organization for Human Rights and the Arab Lawyers Union and the
Arab Journalists Unions agreed to join efforts in protecting the
holy city from Israeli violations, the report said.
</P>
<P>
The plan of action includes a wide-scale media campaign to
enhance awareness of the Arab and Islamic characteristics of
Jerusalem, the third holiest site of Islam.
</P>
<P>
The groups decided to form a team of experts to prepare an
integrated document on Jerusalem and its political, legal and
religious aspects.
</P>
<P>
They expressed readiness to uphold the Arab right to the
traditional Arab East Jerusalem and promote the Palestinians'
legitimate struggle to establish an independent state with East
Jerusalem as its capital.
</P>
<P>
The United Nations' resolutions stipulate that Jerusalem is
under its control. But Israel captured the whole of the city in
wars with Arabs and declared in 1980 that Jerusalem was its
"eternal and undivided capital."
</P>
<P>
The Palestinians want East Jerusalem as capital of their future
independent state.
</P>
<P>
The two sides have begun negotiations for a final peace
agreement on the thorny issues including Jerusalem and the
Palestinians statehood. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
