<HEADLINE> Peru's President Praises Peoples Republic of China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LIMA, September 29 (Xinhua) -- Peruvian President Alberto
Fujimori Wednesday said that the founding of the Peoples Republic
of China, in 1949, was one of the "most important and decisive"
events of this century in political, economic, social and cultural
orders.
</P>
<P>
China, an ancient nation and the highest populated country on
the face of the earth, decided its destiny 50 years ago, turning
into reality the free determination of the people and their right
to this progress and happiness, said Fujimori in a supplement of
the local newspaper "El Commercio", for the celebration of the
50th Anniversary of the People's Republic of China.
</P>
<P>
Since then, China has fought boldly to turn itself into a
developed economy, achieving in the last 20 years a rhythm which
is becoming closer and closer to its objective, he added.
</P>
<P>
For the Peruvians, this constitutes a motive of admiration and
respect for the results of modernization and economic reform in
China, as well as its outlook for the 21st century.  
</P>
</TEXT>
