<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Head-On Collision Leaves Seven Dead in Argentina </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES, September 29 (Xinhua) -- Seven people died and
forty were injured in a head-on collision between a microbus and a
truck with a trailer on Wednesday in Buenos Aires.
</P>
<P>
According to the police, the accident occurred in the morning
when a micro-bus carrying fifty passengers, which was on a run from
Tucuman to Mar del Plata, collided head-on with a Mercedes Benz
truck with a trailer loaded with stone.
</P>
<P>
Because of the strong impact, the truck caught fire at the rear
but the flames spread quickly all over the truck, finally burning
it entirely, causing the death of the driver.
</P>
<P>
The driver of the micro-bus also died along with three
passengers on impact, and a further two passengers died a little
after their arrival to a hospital.
</P>
<P>
Forty other passengers were also injured in the collision. The
cause of the accident is still unknown. 
</P>
</TEXT>
