<HEADLINE> Iran Launches War Games in Gulf of Oman </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, September 29 (Xinhua) -- Iran staged the third phase of
the "Ettehad 78" maneuvers in the Gulf of Oman early Wednesday in
which submarines and naval ships of the army posed for
confrontation with the attack of a hypothetical enemy.
</P>
<P>
Simultaneous with the submersion of the submarines, other units
of the group intercepted and repelled air raids by fighter jets of
the hypothetical enemy with air defense systems and electronic war
equipment, said spokesman of the war games Admiral Abdollah
Ma'navi.
</P>
<P>
Commander of the Naval Forces of the Army Admiral Abbas Mohtaj
and a number of other commanders observed a parade by the vessels
and fighter jets.
</P>
<P>
Technical experts and observers believe that the maneuvers have
so far been carried out successfully, said Ma'navi.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman told the Islamic Republic News Agency (IRNA) ON
Tuesday night that the maneuvers have so far caused no nuisance
and no message has been sent by foreign vessels cruising in the
area.
</P>
<P>
He said that 80 vessels of the 5th Fleet of the U.S. Navy in
the Persian Gulf waters have caused pollution to the environment.
</P>
</TEXT>
