<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Qian Qichen Meets Hong Kong, Macao Dignitaries </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 29 (Xinhua) -- Chinese vice premier Qian
Qichen met here today with a dozen of dignitaries from the Hong
Kong Special Administrative Region (HKSAR) and Macao.
</P>
<P>
The people are leaders of nine delegations from HKSAR and Macao
to visit Beijing and attend celebration activities to mark the
50th founding anniversary of the People's Republic of China.
</P>
<P>
Welcoming the visitors, Qian said that it is over two years
after Hong Kong's return to the motherland. Under guideline of "
one country, two systems" policy, HKSAR keeps on stability and
prosperity during the period, he said.
</P>
<P>
The participation of the Macao people in preparing the
government of Macao Special Administrative Region has made
considerable contribution to Macao's smooth return and continuous
development, Qian said.
</P>
<P>
Addressing the Taiwan issue, Qian emphasized that China will
adhere to the basic principles of 'peaceful reunification' and '
one country, two systems' and to the eight-point proposal put
forward by President Jiang Zemin in 1995.
</P>
<P>
Jiang has extended concern and condolence to victims of the
recent earthquake that rocked Taiwan, Qian said, noting that the
mainland is willing to offer any possible assistance.
</P>
<P>
Abundant cash and materials have been donated by people on the
mainland as the Chinese people on both sides of the Taiwan Straits
are as closely linked as flesh and blood, Qian added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
