<DOCNO> XIE19990930.0030 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-30 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hong Kong Re-gearing for 21st Century: Anson Chan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, September 29 (Xinhua) -- Administrative Secretary of
the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (HKSAR) Anson Chan
said here Wednesday that Hong Kong is now re-gearing and re-
tooling for the 21st century.
</P>
<P>
Despite the slings and arrows of the last two-and-a-quarter
years, Hong Kong has not lost its way, but is simply engaged in a
process of renewal, she said, while delivering a speech at the
luncheon meeting of the Foreign Correspondents' Club.
</P>
<P>
"We have not abandoned the values on which we have built our
past success," she stressed.
</P>
<P>
"So long as we continue to enjoy - and more importantly protect
- our promised high degree of autonomy and remain united in our
efforts, then I see no good reason why Hong Kong should not forge
ahead economically, socially and politically and maintain our
position as Asia's premier international city," she said.
</P>
<P>
On the economy side, Chan said that the HKSAR government has
formulated, in a difficult environment, two very pro-active
Budgets that helped alleviate some of the financial pain being
felt by many in the community. The effects of those measures are
now starting to trickle through, as evidenced by the recent signs
of a pickup in consumer sentiment.
</P>
<P>
The government's policy has always been characterized as
positive non-interventionism. The government does not intervene
unless it is in the overall public interest to do so. Its
involvement in the Cyberport is a natural extension of this
process, she said.
</P>
<P>
"We are, after all, facing a revolution as potentially profound
in its impact on humanity as the Industrial Revolution. And for us
to sit on our hands debating the niceties of positive non-
interventionism when a serious entrepreneurial opportunity is
presented to us would not, I fear in the final analysis, win us
any plaudits in this practical and progressive community," she
said.
</P>
<P>
Noting that there is so much misguided talk about the Cyberport
being a sweetheart property deal, she said: "Some people have lost
track of what we have achieved at a stroke: a quality development
which will be wholly owned by the government and which has already
attracted 12 big hi-tech names as anchor tenants, at minimum
government outlay, with the potential for handsome profits for the
taxpayers, in addition to the creation of a strategic cluster of
information technology and service companies which will provide us
with a front-grid position in the fast-moving digital world."
</P>
<P>
"What we have is a cyber based platform to help Hong Kong go up
the value chain," she stated.
</P>
<P>
Stressing that the government has an open mind about the right
way forward, Chan called on the community and media
representatives at all levels to express their views freely.
</P>
<P>
With regard to the issue of the rule of law, Chan noted that
the preservation of the rule of law must be Hong Kong's top
priority.
</P>
<P>
"We all instinctively know that our deeply-rooted legal system
and our independent judiciary sets us apart from the rest of Asia.
So does our free and prolific press," she added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990930.0031 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-30 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 1600 GMT, September 29 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA -- A total of 13 rebels of the outlawed Kurdish Workers'
Party (PKK) were killed in recent military operations in
southeastern Turkey, an official statement said on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The statement, issued by the office of the Emergency Rule
Region, said that the Turkish security forces killed three PKK
militants at Kolludere village in Hizan town of Bitlis province,
seven in Semdinli town of Hakkari province, one in Ovacik town of
Tunceli province and two in Catak town of Van province. (Turkey-
PKK)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
BEIRUT -- A member of the pro-Israeli South Lebanon Army (SLA)
was killed and two others were wounded Wednesday in south Lebanon,
Lebanese security sources said.
</P>
<P>
The fatality occurred when the country's leading guerrilla
group Hezbollah launched attacks on the militia's outpost at Rshaf
inside the Israeli occupied border zone in south Lebanon. (
Lebanon-SLA-Killed)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
BAGHDAD -- Meetings of the third session of the Iraqi-Russian
Economic, Trade and Technical Joint Committee started here on
Wednesday, the Iraqi News Agency (INA) reported.
</P>
<P>
The meetings were co-chaired by Iraqi Oil Minister Amir
Muhammad Rashid and visiting Russian Minister of Fuel and Energy
Victor Kalyuzhni, who arrived here on Tuesday evening, leading a
large delegation. (Iraq-Russia-Economic Cooperation)
</P>
<P>
