</P>
<P>
NEW DELHI -- Militants fired a barrage of rifle grenades at the
Secretariat complex in Srinagar of Kashmir, in a bid to blow up
the heavily-guarded multi-storied building.
</P>
<P>
Local officials said that seven people, mostly securitymen,
were injured as six grenades landed in and around the complex in
quick succession at around 1045 hours local time. (India-Kashmir)
