<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-30 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Construction of Large Sewage Disposal Plant </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SUZHOU, September 29 (Xinhua) -- Construction work on a 150-
million-yuan sewage treatment plant commenced today in Suzhou, a
renowned tourist destination in east China's Jiangsu Province.
</P>
<P>
The plant is scheduled to be built up in the year 2001 and is
able to serve 250,000 citizens by disposing 80,000 cu m of sewage
per day.
</P>
<P>
The operation of the plant will make it possible for more than
50 percent of sewage from local urbanites to be treated, a big
rise from the current 19.15 percent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
