<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-30 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> President Jiang Zemin on Ethnic Work (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 29 (Xinhua) -- From now till the year 2010,
the ethnic work in China will focus on speeding up economic and
social development in where people of ethnic groups live and
strengthening the unity of all nationalities and social stability,
said President Jiang Zemin here today.
</P>
<P>
Jiang made the remarks at the opening ceremony of the third
national conference to commend individuals and organizations for
promoting ethnic unity and progress.
</P>
<P>
He said that to promote the development of ethnic minority
groups and of areas inhabited by ethnic minorities will help
narrow the gaps between the development of various areas across
the country and realize common prosperity of the whole nation.
</P>
<P>
The government should give vigorous support to areas inhabited
by ethnic minorities which are still left far behind by
economically-developed coastal areas, and introduce more fund,
advanced technology and talented people to those areas with
favorable policies, Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
He said that China should help ethnic minority areas build some
infrastructure facilities including water conservancy, transport,
telecommunications and energy supply which will play important
roles in economic development.
</P>
<P>
China should improve the poverty-elimination work in ethnic
minority areas and further promote the development of the central
and western regions where most of the ethnic minority groups live,
he stressed.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said that education in those areas should be improved,
with more knowledge of science and technology spreading to ethnic
minority people, and higher learning and research institutes
should be encouraged to provide more scientific and technological
results to the areas.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990930.0035 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-30 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> President Jiang Zemin on Ethnic Work (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Jiang noted that China should pursue and improve the system of
regional autonomy of ethnic minority groups and cultivate and
promote more officials of ethnic minority origin.
</P>
<P>
He said that the regional autonomy ethnic minority groups is a
basic political system in China and should be adhered to
steadfastly and improved constantly.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said that the government should safeguard the regional
autonomy of ethnic minorities according to law and ethnic
autonomous regions should follow the principles and policies of
the Chinese Communist Party and the central government.
</P>
<P>
He also stressed the importance for improving the legal system
for the ethnic work, and creating a better environment for the
reform, development and stability of autonomous regions and areas.
</P>
<P>
He said that more middle-aged and young officials from the
ethnic minority groups should be selected and more ethnic minority
people in science and technology and economic management should be
trained.
</P>
<P>
The president called on officials from all ethnic groups to
unite and respect, support and learn from each other to contribute
to the economic and social development of ethnic minority areas.
</P>
<P>
Jiang stressed that China should strengthen the unity of all
ethnic groups and safeguard the unification and social stability
of the country.
</P>
<P>
He said that contradictions among various ethnic groups and in
ethnic areas should be properly dealt with and disputes over the
benefits of various ethnic groups should be solved promptly.  (
more)

nnnn
</P>
</TEXT>
