<BODY>
<HEADLINE> President Jiang Zemin on Ethnic Work (3) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
To safeguard the unification of the motherland and fight
against ethnic splittism is a long-term political task, Jiang
pointed out, adding that it is an old trick of the Western anti-
China forces to use ethnic and religious issues to westernize and
split up China.
</P>
<P>
We should unite and depend on officials and ordinary people
from various ethnic groups to isolate and fight against a handful
of ethnic separatists, and prevent and combat the infiltration of
the foreign anti-China forces, Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
He said that we should implement the policy of freedom of
religious belief and strengthen the guidance and management of
religious affairs in accordance with law.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said that China should uphold and strengthen the Party's
leadership on ethnic work, and continue to improve the work.
</P>
<P>
Party organizations at grass-root level should further increase
contacts with people from various ethnic groups and lead them to
develop production, eliminate poverty and improve the unity of
ethnic groups.
</P>
<P>
The Central Committee of the Chinese Communist Party calls on
the 56 ethnic groups in China to hold up high the great banner of
Marxism, Leninism, Mao Zedong Thought and Deng Xiaoping Theory,
and to strive to promote the unity and progress of ethnic groups
for the rejuvenation of the Chinese nation, Jiang said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
