<HEADLINE> Tanzania Congratulates China on Its 50th </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, September 29 (Xinhua) -- Tanzanian President
Benjamin Mkapa Wednesday sent a message to his Chinese counterpart
Jiang Zemin, congratulating the 50th anniversary of the founding
of the People's Republic of China.
</P>
<P>
"On behalf of the government and the people of the United
Republic of Tanzania, it gives me great pleasure to extend to you
and through you to the people of China my warm and heartfelt
congratulations," he said in the message.
</P>
<P>
Mkapa expressed Tanzania's determination to further develop and
 strengthen the existing friendly relations and cooperation
between the two countries for mutual benefit of the two peoples.
</P>
<P>
He also reiterated his appreciation for China's contribution to
the development process of Tanzania, wishing steady progress and
prosperity for the Chinese people. 
