delegation from Japan-China Association for Cultural Exchange
headed by its president Dan Ikuma, and expressed appreciation on
Dan's contribution to the advancement of the understanding and
friendship between the people of China and Japan.
</P>
<P>
 Chinese Vice-Premier Meets Cambodian Visitors
</P>
<P>
-- Chinese Vice-Premier Li Lanqing said here today in a meeting
with a Cambodian delegation headed by Princess Norodom Buppa Devi,
minister of Culture and Art of Cambodia, that China and Cambodia
enjoy a long-term traditional friendship, and bilateral relations
in various fields have registered constant development in recent
years. He voiced the hope that Sino-Cambodian cultural exchanges
would be strengthened.
</P>
<P>
 Chinese Vice President Meets Malian Guests
</P>
<P>
-- Hu Jintao, Chinese vice president and vice chairman of the
Central Military Commission, met with Malian Defense Minister
Mohamed Salia Sokona here this afternoon.
</P>
<P>
Hu said that both countries have deep traditional friendship
and good relations. The cooperation between the two countries and
the two armed forces has been "fruitful," he said, adding that the
Chinese government was grateful for the consistent support of the
Malian government regarding such issues as Taiwan and human rights.
</P>
<P>
 Sokona reiterated that the Malian government will
unswervingly adhere to the "one China" stance.
</P>
<P>
 NPC Chairman Meets Famous Chinese-American
</P>
<P>
-- Li Peng, chairman of the Standing Committee of the Chinese
National People's Congress, met with famous Chinese-American and
President of the U.S. Committee for International Cooperation Anna
Chan Chennault, here today.
</P>
<P>
Li welcomed Chan on her visit at this historic time of the 50th
anniversary of the founding of the People's Republic of China.
</P>
<P>
He spoke highly of her consistent efforts in improving
relations across the Taiwan Straits and promoting education in
China. He also briefed Chan on China's present economic condition.
</P>
