had had "constructive contact" with Sinn Fein and expected to
arrange a meeting in the near future.
</P>
<P>
He was responding to a Sinn Fein call for a meeting with Tory
leader William Hague.
</P>
<P>
McGuinness, Sinn Fein's chief negotiator, said he would welcome
the "opening of dialogue" with the Conservative leadership. But he
requested a formal session of talks because he said discussions
would give the Conservatives a wider picture of the peace process
and not the narrow sectional view he said they now had.
</P>
<P>
The review of the Northern Ireland peace process will resume
Thursday. 
</P>
