<HEADLINE> LIFFE To Launch Option On FTSE EuroTop 100 Index </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, September 29 (Xinhua) -- The London International
Financial Futures and Options Exchange (LIFFE) Wednesday announced
it will launch an option contract on the FTSE Eurotop 100 Index on
18 October.
</P>
<P>
LIFFE Chief Executive Hugh Freedberg said, "LIFFE's new FTSE
Eurotop 100 Options contract will complement the FTSE Eurotop 100
Futures contract, LIFFE's longest running pan-European stock index
contract."
</P>
<P>
"Since its launch in May 1998, the futures contract has seen a
spectacular growth in volume of 187 percent year on year and open
interest recently touched 1 billion euros by value," he added.
</P>
<P>
The LIFFE offers the widest range of futures and options on
pan-European stock indices, allowing customers to choose the right
stock index products for trading and hedging their preferred
pan-European equity index benchmark.
</P>
<P>
It is believed here that the launch of this option contract
will further support the LIFFE's customers active in the
underlying futures contract. 
</P>
</TEXT>
