<HEADLINE> Malaysia Lashes out Power Politics </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, September 29 (Xinhua) -- Malaysia on Wednesday
criticized the unequal world order which allows the powerful
nations to set the rule for others.
</P>
<P>
Prime Minister Mahathir Mohamad said with the end of the Cold
War "the liberal democratic free market capitalists see no more
need to be gentle in spreading their systems or in profiting from
them".
</P>
<P>
He said today no one would be allowed any other political or
economic system except what is prescribed by the sole dominant
bloc.
</P>
<P>
"The true ugliness of Western capitalism reveiled itself,
backed by the military might of capitalism's greatest proponent,"
he said.
</P>
<P>
The last decade of the 20th century saw the "moral endorsement"
of the right of the powerful to interference in any country's
internal affairs, Mahathir said.
</P>
<P>
"Systems of government and the administration of justice, of
the financial and commercial systems came under the scrutiny of
the powerful countries," he added.
</P>
<P>
In a reference to the United States, Mahathir said: "a
President decided that his country had a right and a duty to
oversee that human rights are not abused anywhere in the world
irrespective of borders and the independence of nations."
</P>
<P>
The out-spoken Malaysian leader said the "big and the powerful"
country often bypassed the United Nations in deciding when to step
in and when to step out.
</P>
<P>
He accused in a indirect way the U.S. of conducting so-called
tele-wars using high technology such as the pinpoint bombings in
order to avoid the body bags from coming home while unnecessarily
killing innocent people and destroying wrong targets. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
