<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-30 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Calls for Adequate World Attention to Africa </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, September 29 (Xinhua) -- China Wednesday called
on the international community to pay adequate attention to
Africa, to create a favorable external environment for African
development, and to take concrete steps to assist African
countries in their development endeavor.
</P>
<P>
The statement came as Qin Huasun, Chinese permanent
representative to the United Nations, took the floor at the
Security Council, which convened an open meeting on Africa.
</P>
<P>
First, the international community should pay adequate
attention to Africa from a strategic height, he said.
</P>
<P>
"Without stability and prosperity on the African continent,
there will be no peace and development in the world," he said.
"Thus to ensure world peace and development, it is vital to help
African countries maintain stability and pursue development."
</P>
<P>
"The international community should treat Africa a an equal
development partner and give energetic support and assistance to
African countries in their various endeavors," he said.
</P>
<P>
Secondly, the international community should create favorable
external environment for Africa so that it may enjoy stability and
sustained development, he said.
</P>
<P>
"For too long, Africa has not been given due concern and
attention in international affairs and has been delegated to the
lowest level of international division of labor," he said.
</P>
<P>
"What is worse, in the high wave of globalization, Africa is in
danger of being marginalized," he said, "If this situation were
not to be corrected, there would be no peace and development in
Africa to talk about."
</P>
<P>
Thirdly, the international community should respect the choice
made by African countries themselves, he said.
</P>
<P>
"The world is diversified and even so on the African
continent," he said. "Due to different national conditions, issue
of the same nature may take different manifestations in different
countries and at different times."
</P>
<P>
"In our efforts to help Africa, the international community
must take into account the specific condition and specific need of
various African countries and peoples," Qin said. "Uniform models
coming from outside do not necessarily fit the actual conditions
of different African countries."
</P>
<P>
"The imposition of one set model and attachment of political
conditions while providing assistance would not really help
African countries get out of their predicament," he said.
</P>
<P>
Fourthly, the international community should give vigorous
support to efforts by varying regional organizations in Africa, he
said.
</P>
<P>
"We call on the international community to further support and
cooperate with regional organizations in conflict prevention and
settlement, and provide necessary assistance in cash and in kind
without political conditions to security and peacekeeping
humanitarianism in Africa," he said.
</P>
<P>
Last but not the least, the international community should take
concrete and meaningful actions to help Africa countries in their
development endeavor, he said.
</P>
<P>
"We call on countries around the world, especially developed
countries, to help Africa by making good their commitment of
official development aid, reducing the debt burden of African
countries and withdrawing some of their trade barriers," he said.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
