<DOCNO> XIE19990930.0076 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-30 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Wall Street Stocks Fall Again </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, September 29 (Xinhua) -- Wall Street stocks fell
Wednesday for the second straight session as investors worried
about the possibility of heigher interest rates a few days before
the Federal Reserve meets on the monetary policy.
</P>
<P>
The Dow Jones industrial average closed down 62.05 at
10,213.48, adding to a loss of 27.86 points Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Broader stock indicators were mostly lower. The Standard &AMP;
Poor's 500 index fell 13.83 at 1,268.37 and the technology heavy
Nasdaq composite index fell 25.98 at 2,730.27.
</P>
<P>
The market moved down as investors were reluctant to step in
buying before the Federal Reserve meets on the interest rates in
Washington on October 5. Concerns with the hike in the rates for
the third time this year have dragged stocks lower this month.
</P>
<P>
Corporate profit warnings also hurt stocks. IBM and
Hewlett-Packard, both the Dow's components, performed poorly in
the market.
</P>
<P>
The NYSE index fell 3.84 at 586.24. But the American Stock
Exchange index rose 7.19 at 780.04 and the Russell 2000 index of
smaller companies rose 3.03 at 421.52.
</P>
<P>
Advancing issues outnumbered decliners by a 10-to-9 margin on
the New York Stock Exchange, with 1,605 up, 1,463 down and 493
unchanged.
</P>
<P>
NYSE volume declined to 850.86 million shares from 876.95
million in the previous session. 
</P>
</TEXT>
