<HEADLINE> Highlights of Today's Diplomatic News in China (3) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
-- The China Red Cross Society (CRCS) will send food and
medicine valued at 100,000 U.S. dollars to East Timor, Chinese
Foreign Ministry Spokeswoman Zhang Qiyue announced here today.
</P>
<P>
In response to a reporter's question, Zhang said the CRCS has
sent the message to the International Committee of the Red Cross,
which will send the aid to the people of East Timor.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Vice-Premier Meets Boeing Boss
</P>
<P>
-- Vice-Premier Wu Bangguo met today with Phil Condit, chairman
and chief executive officer of the Boeing Company. Wu briefed
Condit on the development of China's civil aviation industry, and
said that China's civil aviation sector is willing to promote
cooperation with its foreign counterparts.
</P>
<P>
Condit said that his company is committed to a long-term
development in China, and it is fully prepared to expand areas of
cooperation with the country.
</P>
<P>
Chinese, Russian Presidents Confer By Phone
</P>
<P>
-- Russian President Boris Yeltsin made a phone call to Chinese
President Jiang Zemin this evening to express congratulations on
the occasion of the 50th anniversary of the founding of the People
's Republic of China and the 50th anniversary of the establishment
of Sino-Russian diplomatic ties. The two leaders reiterated their
hope to further reinforce the strategic cooperative partnership
between the two countries.  
</P>
