<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ring-Road Section in Xiamen Opens to Traffic </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XIAMEN, September 30 (Xinhua) -- The second section of the Ring
Road Highway opened to traffic today in this coastal city in
southeast China's Fujian Province.
</P>
<P>
Located in the eastern coastal area of the city, the 12.8-km-
long highway is being built at a cost of 590 million yuan.
</P>
<P>
The second section, which was begun in 1996, is expected to
facilitate the city's transportation and economic development.
</P>
<P>
With an investment of 110 million yuan, the first section of
the highway was opened in 1995, and the third phase is scheduled
to begin next year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
