<HEADLINE> Books on China's Regional Economy Published </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 30 (Xinhua) -- A series of books entitled "
Regional Development: Retrospect and Prospects for China" was
published here today.
</P>
<P>
The series, edited by the State Development and Planning
Commission, systematically explains the regional characteristics
of every province, autonomous region and municipality in the
country.
</P>
<P>
It also details the great achievements scored by the provinces,
autonomous regions, and municipalities in their economic and
social development and opening-up to the outside world.
</P>
<P>
Also included in the series are projections and analyses of
regional economic and social development early next century.
</P>
<P>
The series includes 32 volumes with about 8 million Chinese
words, and a general introduction along with volumes on every
province, autonomous region, and municipality.
</P>
<P>
Chinese President Jiang Zemin inscribed the title of the series.
</P>
</TEXT>
