<HEADLINE> People's Daily Hails PRC's 50th Founding Anniversary (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 30 (Xinhua) -- The "People's Daily" will
carry an editorial in its October 1 issue titled "Long Live the
Motherland," celebrating the 50th anniversary of the founding of
the People's Republic of China (PRC) and calling it a "grand
festival" occurring on the eve of the 21st century.
</P>
<P>
All the Chinese people are indulging in the celebrations and
are bursting with pride for the mightiness of the motherland, the
rejuvenation of the nation, and the brightness of the future, says
the editorial.
</P>
<P>
"The Chinese people have never held their heads so high and
drawn so much attention from all over the world as they do today,"
it says.
</P>
<P>
In the editorial, the country's leading newspaper congratulates
the Chinese people from all walks of life, of different ethnic
groups, Chinese compatriots in Hong Kong, Macao and Taiwan
Province, overseas Chinese, as well as army soldiers and police
officers.
</P>
<P>
It salutes working people, heroes and model individuals who
have made notable contributions to the reinvigoration of new China.
It also remembers national heroes and prominent sons and daughters
of the Chinese nation who have contributed to the country's
emancipation and the birth and building of new China.
</P>
<P>
The editorial calls the birth of new China in 1949 a
fundamental turning point for the fate of the Chinese people, the
end of the semi-feudal and semi-colonial period during which the
Chinese were oppressed and bullied, and the beginning of a new age
for the Chinese nation. It is also a major historical event of the
20th century and has had a profound effect on the political
structure and progress of the modern-day world.
</P>
</TEXT>
