<BODY>
<HEADLINE> People's Daily Hails PRC's 50th Founding Anniversary (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The piece goes on to emphasize that over the past 50 years,
especially the past 20 years since China practiced the reform and
opening-up policy, "earth-shaking" changes have taken place in new
China, noting that under the leadership of the Communist Party of
China (CPC), the Chinese people have experienced the "most shining
chapters of the history of the Chinese civilization."
</P>
<P>
Over the past decades, the editorial says, China has achieved
sustained development of the national economy; greatly
strengthened its integrated national power; witnessed prosperity
in the fields of science and technology, education, and culture,
as well as the overall progress in all social undertakings;
increased its defense capability; created solidarity and
friendliness among people of different ethnic groups; ceaselessly
improved the material, cultural and living standards of the people;
gained major advancement in the great cause of the reunification
of the motherland; and is soon to resume its exercise of
sovereignty over Macao, following the homecoming of Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
The editorial stresses that the key factor for the enormous
changes in new China is the correct leadership of the CPC. For the
sake of invigorating the Chinese nation and completely changing
the fate of the Chinese people, Chinese communists have adopted
the most advanced ideological theory and social system; explored
and mapped out the road of development, principles and policies
that are best adapted to the conditions of China; integrated the
basic principles of Marxism and the reality of China; and created
miracles in the country, one by one.
</P>
<P>
The people feel deeply, based on the great changes in the
country and as a result of their own experience, that the CPC is a
completely selfless party, full of vitality, and constantly
advancing, the editorial says, adding that no other power like the
CPC can bring the Chinese people to a future of affluence,
happiness and hope.
</P>
</TEXT>
