<HEADLINE> Haas Upsets Agassi in Three Sets </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BERLIN, September 30 (Xinhua) -- Tommy Haas of Germany produced
the big surprise by outing top-ranked Andre Agassi in three sets
at the 6.7 million U.S. dollars Grand Clam Cup in Munich on
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
It was the first defeat for Agassi since his victory in the U.S.
Open nearly three weeks ago. The American veteran lost in three
sets of 6-0, 6-7 (2-7), 6-4 in one hour and 40 minutes.
</P>
<P>
The 21-year-old Haas picked up 325,000 U.S. dollars for
reaching the semifinals of the richest tournament in the world.
</P>
<P>
Steffi Graf, the retired star whose romance with Agassi has
dominated German headlines for the past two weeks, was not in
Munich's Olympic hall to watch the match.
</P>
<P>
Agassi regained the No. 1 ranking after winning the U.S. Open.
Also winner of the French Open and a finalist at Wimbledon, Agassi
had come into the tournament having won 35 of his last 39 matches.
</P>
<P>
Agassi, 29, had a bye into the quarterfinals and earned 175,000
U.S. dollars.He also got a bonus of 250,000 U.S. dollars for the
two Grand Slam titles he won this year - the French Open and the U.
S. Open.
</P>
<P>
Munich organizers invite 12 men and eight women with best
records at the four Grand Slam events of the year and offers more
money per head than any other event.
</P>
<P>
The men's winner gets 1.3 million U.S. dollars while the women'
s champion receives 800,000 U.S. dollars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
