<DOCNO> XIE19990930.0112 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-30 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> ADB Approves Road Loan to China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, September 30 (Xinhua) -- The Asian Development Bank
(ADB) approved Thursday a 250 million-U.S.-dollar loan to China
for the country's Shanxi road development project.
</P>
<P>
The ADB said in a news release that the project will construct
176 kilometers of an expressway along the most difficult section
of a highway from the north to the south of Shanxi province.
</P>
<P>
According to the ADB, provincial roads to the expressway
interchanges and country roads to township centers will also be
built and upgraded to provide people better access to schools,
medical, and other social services.
</P>
<P>
The project will directly and indirectly reduce poverty among
the 6.8 million people in the project area, said the ADB.
</P>
<P>
The total cost of the project is estimated at 726.1 million
U.S. dollars and the balance of the cost will be borne by the
Provincial Government, Ministry of Communications, and Bank of
Communications.
</P>
<P>
The loan is repayable over 24 years, including a grace period
of four years, with an annual commitment charge of 0.75 percent,
said the ADB. 
</P>
</TEXT>
