<HEADLINE> China Welcomes More Foreign Experts: Premier </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 30 (Xinhua) -- Premier Zhu Rongji said here
today that China welcomes more foreign experts to come and work
for and participate in the country's socialist modernization.
</P>
<P>
Zhu was speaking to 100 foreign experts, overseas Chinese
experts, and international friends of China who won the "
Friendship Prize" for 1999 awarded by the Chinese government.
</P>
<P>
He said China will continue to carry on the policy of inviting
overseas experts, and will endeavor to create more attractive
working environments and conditions.
</P>
<P>
The premier expressed warm congratulations on behalf of the
Chinese government and people for the honor they have received,
saying that foreign experts have helped China in the achievements
made over the past 50 years.
</P>
<P>
According to the State Administration of Foreign Experts
Affairs, China has hired a total of 800,000 foreign experts since
1949. The majority of them came to China after the country began
the policy of reform and opening to the outside world 20 years ago.
</P>
<P>
The "Friendship Prize" was first awarded in 1991 to foreign
experts for their outstanding achievements in China. A total of
524 foreign experts from 49 countries and regions have won this
award.  
</P>
</TEXT>
