<HEADLINE> Beijing Parks Ready for National Day Carnival </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 30 (Xinhua) -- Elaborately decorated, the
major parks in the Chinese capital have been readied to embrace
the joyful celebrants of China's 50th birthday anniversary.
</P>
<P>
Potted flowers, colorful flags and red lanterns have beautified
the parks, where fountains and stages have also have been erected
to create festive atmosphere.
</P>
<P>
"The city's 10 large parks are expected to receive nearly two
million visitors during the next five days, the largest crowds
Beijing parks have ever had during the National Day holiday," said
an official at the bureau directing park activities.
</P>
<P>
Top Chinese leaders will be among the parks' visitors, he added.
</P>
<P>
Visiting parks is a traditional part of National Day
celebrations for Beijing residents, and this year a grand formal
parade and an evening carnival at Tian'anmen Square are also on
the agenda for tomorrow.
</P>
<P>
Most of the parks are also popular tourist spots in Beijing,
including the Temple of Heaven, the Summer Palace, Beihai Park,
and Jingshan Park north to the Forbidden City.
</P>
<P>
The parks are decorated to reflect different themes, said the
official. For example, Zhongshan Park at the western side of the
Tian'anmen Rostrum, has been turned into a sea of flowers by some
100,000 potted flowers and huge floral arrangements, which suggest
a rosy future for the country.
</P>
<P>
Other special sights for visitors include a dragon-boat
contests on the lake at the Summer Palace, a birthday-cake-shaped
fountain at Jingshan Park, and a photo exhibit at the Beijing
Working People's Palace of Culture, displaying achievements in
China over the past 50 years.
</P>
<P>
Entertainment programs will bring visitors different cultural
experiences as performers stage dances of various ethnic minority
groups in China, and those of foreign countries as well.
</P>
<P>
However, the official said, the five parks near Tian'anmen
Square will be closed tomorrow in order to facilitate the parade
and the evening gala on the Square. These are the parks of
Zhongshan, Beihai, Jingshan, the Temple of Heaven, and the Beijing
People's Palace of Culture.  
</P>
</TEXT>
