<HEADLINE> Yeltsin Praises China For Great Achievements </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, September 30 (Xinhua) -- Russian President Boris
Yeltsin on Thursday praised China for its great achievements in
the past five decades as well as the smooth development of Russian-
Sino relations.
</P>
<P>
In a written interview with Xinhua on the eve of the 50th
anniversary of the founding of the People's Republic of China and
the establishment of diplomatic ties between Moscow and Beijing,
Yeltsin noted that China's gross domestic product (GDP) went up by
200 times while people's living standards witnessed fundamental
improvements over the past 50 years.
</P>
<P>
Industrial output grew by 158 times during the same period as
the basis for a market economy takes shape.
</P>
<P>
The achievements have invoked the Chinese people's sense of
pride and won worldwide recognition, Yeltsin said.
</P>
<P>
The People's Republic of China was founded on October 1, 1949,
and China's diplomatic relations with the Soviet Union was
established two days later.
</P>
<P>
The president said China's success in reforms and development
has shown that any country, especially those with a vast expanse
of territory and a huge population, should pursue its own road of
reform and that simply copying other country's modes will not
arrive at an ideal outcome.
</P>
<P>
China's achievements also indicated that respect for one's own
characteristics and emphasis on self-reliance do not mean self-
isolation. China has sustained smooth development and secured its
rightful place in the world community because it has been pursuing
an opening-up policy that absorbs all best experiences from world
civilizations.
</P>
<P>
He said the Chinese leadership's political will and resolution
are the key prerequisites for China's success in reforms.
</P>
<P>
Chinese leaders are among the most pragmatic ones and are never
dizzied with success; they would place even more emphasis on the
unresolved problems when they are enjoying the most advantageous
times. This way of thinking and doing things deserves great
respect, Yeltsin said.
</P>
<P>
He said that strategies and social-economic institutions are
already in place for China to ensure its continued smooth and
overall development in the new millennium.
</P>
<P>
Yeltsin expressed the belief that China's political and
economic influences on the world would grow steadily in the 21st
century.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
