<HEADLINE> Grand Reception Marks 50th Founding Anniversary of PRC </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 30 (Xinhua) -- China's State Council held a
grand reception marking the 50th anniversary of the founding of
the People's Republic of China at the Great Hall of the People
here this evening.
</P>
<P>
President Jiang Zemin and other Chinese Communist Party and
state leaders, including Li Peng, Zhu Rongji, Li Ruihuan, Hu
Jintao, Wei Jianxing and Li Lanqing, attended the reception
together with some 5,000 other people.
</P>
<P>
Premier Zhu Rongji in his address at the reception extended
festive congratulations to people of all ethnic groups in China
who have been working hard on all fronts and cordial greeting to
compatriots in the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region, Macao,
Taiwan and abroad on behalf of the Central Committee of the
Communist Party of China (CPC) and the State Council.
</P>
<P>
"I would also like to sincerely thank our foreign friends
present here and all other international friends who have shown
great interest in and rendered their support to China's reform,
opening-up and modernization drive," he said.
</P>
<P>
In his speech, Zhu reviewed China's achievements during the
past five decades, and talked about China's current domestic
situation, Macao's return, the Taiwan issue and China's foreign
policy.
</P>
<P>
Reviewing the past and looking to the future, the premier said,
"We have full confidence in the success of the cause of our
country and our nation. The road ahead will by no means be smooth
and there will inevitably be problems and difficulties."
</P>
<P>
He believed, however, that "we remain convinced that under the
guidance of Deng Xiaoping Theory and the strong leadership of the
CPC Central Committee with Comrade Jiang Zemin as the core, the
people of China will surely be able to triumph over all
difficulties, realize the grand cross-century objectives for
socialist modernization and promote the great rejuvenation of the
Chinese nation."
</P>
<P>
Wang Zhongyu, state councillor and secretary-general of the
State Council, presided over the reception.
</P>
<P>
Prior to the reception, Jiang Zemin and other top Party and
state leaders met with representatives of model workers, model
soldiers, military and police officers, model public servants and
representatives of ethnic groups. 
</P>
