<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Yeltsin: Russia-China Ties Face Bright Vistas </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, September 30 (Xinhua) -- Russian President Boris
Yeltsin said Thursday that Russia-China relations based on a
strategic partnership of cooperation face bright vistas in the
21st century.
</P>
<P>
In a written interview with Xinhua on the eve of the 50th
anniversary of the founding of the People's Republic of China (PRC)
and the establishment of diplomatic ties between Moscow and
Beijing, Yeltsin said the two country's keeping their deeds in
line with words is a guarantee for the bright prospects in
bilateral ties.
</P>
<P>
The PRC was founded on October 1, 1949, and its diplomatic
relations with the Soviet Union was established two days later.
</P>
<P>
He summed up eight points of experience in the development of
ties between Moscow and Beijing over the five decades. They are:
</P>
<P>
-- Their unity, territorial integrity, stability and prosperity
serve the interests of both countries;
</P>
<P>
-- Whatever the trends in world affairs, bilateral ties should
remain among the priorities in the two countries' diplomatic front.
An underestimation of the importance of bilateral ties would
always harm the fundamental interests of the two countries.
</P>
<P>
-- Respect for each other's choice of development road is
indispensable to mutual trust and consolidation of bilateral
relations;
</P>
<P>
-- The mode of ties that optimally serves the interests of both
Russia and China is a comprehensive and constructive partnership
of cooperation based on equality and aiming against no third
states or state groupings;
</P>
<P>
-- The main direction in further consolidating Russia-China
ties should be a fundamental improvement in methods of trade and
economic cooperation and an enlargement of the scale of such
cooperation;
</P>
<P>
-- The guarantees for the two country's security should be
based on ever broadening and consolidated mutual trust in the
military and political fields and on multi-faceted cooperation in
the economic front;
</P>
<P>
-- Russia and China share a host of close or identical
interests in the establishment of a multi-polar world, and the two
countries should broaden their collaboration in pressing
international issues;
</P>
<P>
-- The two sides should improve and expand their personnel
exchanges.
</P>
<P>
The high level of trust along their common borders has also set
an example for many other countries in the world, he said.
</P>
<P>
He also recalled with warm sentiment his last meeting with
Jiang in Bishkek, Kyrgyzstan, in August, when the two leaders
agreed to strengthen cooperation in fighting regional terrorism,
ethnic separatism and organized crime. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
