<HEADLINE> Kenyan President Attends China's National Day </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, September 30 (Xinhua) -- Kenyan President Daniel arap
Moi and Vice-President George Saitoti Thursday attended a
reception hosted by the Chinese ambassador to Kenya An Yongyu to
celebrate the 50th anniversary of the founding of the People's
Republic of China.
</P>
<P>
"China and Kenya have maintained warm and friendly relations
since our independence", Moi said, adding that China was among the
first countries to establish diplomatic ties with Kenya soon after
Kenya's independence in 1963.
</P>
<P>
Moi also noted that the exchange of visits by the heads of the
two states since 1980s has enhanced the political, cultural and
economic cooperation between the two sides.
</P>
<P>
"Kenya and China share similar views on many international
issues," the president said, adding"at the political level, Kenya
upholds the 'one China' policy and welcomes the forthcoming return
of Macao to the People's Republic of China on December 20, 1999."
</P>
<P>
The president expressed his desire for the existing cooperation
to be further strengthened for mutual benefits between the two
countries and peoples.
</P>
<P>
Chinese ambassador An briefed the guests the achievements China
has made in various fields over the past 50 years and highly spoke
of the cordial relationship between China and Kenya.
</P>
<P>
Attending the reception were more than 500 guests including
Kenyan cabinet ministers and other top officials, the U.N.
officials and diplomatic envoys of various countries based in the
Kenyan capital Nairobi. 
