<DOCNO> XIE19990930.0125 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-30 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Feature: 14 Years on, World Still Divided on Terrorism </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, September 30 (Xinhua) -- The 14th Symposium on
International Terrorism concluded Thursday in Colombo, the capital
of Sri Lanka, with a recommendation to be presented to the general
assembly of the International Criminal Police Organization
(Interpol) in Seoul in November this year.
</P>
<P>
However, after 14 years of symposium on international
terrorism, the international community is still divided on how to
define terrorism and what groups should be designated as terrorist
organizations.
</P>
<P>
Analysts here said how to define terrorism and designate
terrorist organizations are tricky problems as they get involved
in state interests, national consciousness and double standard
adopted by certain western countries.
</P>
<P>
As a compromise the Interpol has aimed to seek international
cooperation against concrete terrorist activities including
hijacking, suicide bombing, killing of innocent civilians and the
funding of terrorists.
</P>
<P>
The three-day symposium, focusing on financing of international
terrorism, has been organized under the auspices of Interpol and
was attended by 77 delegates from 5 international organizations
and 37 countries and regions, including Britain, Canada, China,
China's Hong Kong, France, Germany, South Africa, Sri Lanka and
the United States.
</P>
<P>
Interpol Secretary General Raymond Kendall told the
inauguration ceremony on Tuesday that the world fight against
terrorism may be a little easier now as state sponsorship was on
the decline.
</P>
<P>
Delegates said terrorists were funding their organizations by
drug trafficking, money laundering, human smuggling, hostage
taking, arms trading and deals involving political asylum seekers.
</P>
<P>
Sri Lankan acting Defense Minister Anuruddha Ratwatte told the
symposium, "what is alarming is that these illegal processes have
formed into a vicious network of a transnational character, which
sustains terrorism in all parts of the world."
</P>
<P>
He said, "in this context, the international community has
identified financing of terrorism as a matter of grave concern
which demands immediate attention by all states."
</P>
<P>
Delegates said the United States, Britain, France and Sri Lanka
has been actively promoting international cooperation in
Interpol's member states to refrain from financing, encouraging,
or supporting terrorist activities.
</P>
<P>
Terrorism has been viewed as a threat to national security in
the United States which annually spends about 7 billion U.S.
dollars in combating terrorist activities.
</P>
<P>
The U.S. State Department has designated 39 foreign groups as
terrorist organizations including Sri Lanka's separatist
Liberation Tigers of Tamil Eelam (LTTE).
</P>
<P>
The designation of LTTE as a terrorist organization by the
United States in 1997 has been viewed as Sri Lanka's major
diplomatic triumph.
</P>
<P>
During the symposium, much emphasis has been put on Sri Lanka's
LTTE, Spain's ETA, Turkey's PKK and Yugoslavia's KLA, all
separatist movements in their fight to independence.
</P>
<P>
Nevertheless, the international combat of terrorism is destined
to be hampered due to the longstanding problem of how to define
terrorism.
</P>
<P>
In South Asia alone, there are different opinions on how to
define terrorism. Pakistan delegates are of the view that national
liberation movement should be separated from terrorism,
disagreeing with India.
</P>
<P>
Recently the two arch-rivals have also traded accusations over
what they alleged the other side's support to terrorism.
</P>
<P>
On September 23, in response to the recent Indian move to
portray Pakistan as a country sponsoring terrorism, a senior
official of Pakistani Foreign Ministry said Pakistan has evidence
that India intelligence agency RAW had been involved in terrorism
in Pakistani cities.
</P>
<P>
He said that Pakistan never support terrorism. "Instead we
always condemned terrorism. However, there is a clear distinction
between terrorism and people's struggle to fight for their right
of self-determination," the official said while referring to
Kashmir.
</P>
<P>
The official claimed that Pakistan has enough evidence to take
on India and prove its involvement in sponsoring terrorism in
other South Asian countries. He said RAW has been involved in
establishing of the LTTE, a separatist outfit in Sri Lanka.
</P>
<P>
Sri Lanka, the host country of the 14th symposium, has been
plagued by a 16-year-old civil war between the government troops
and the LTTE rebels who have been fighting for a separate Tamil
homeland in the country's north and east.
</P>
<P>
For Sri Lanka, the funding of LTTE is a matter of vital
importance as it will decide on how long the long-running ethnic
civil war will drag on. The LTTE's complex overseas fund-raising
network has enabled it to survive the government's economic
sanctions and successive military offensives and has been the
headache of the government.
</P>
<P>
Despite much controversy about how to define terrorism, the
symposium still raised some hopes of securing a less dangerous
world we are living in.
</P>
<P>
"This symposium,...stressed the need to strengthen further
international cooperation between states and between international
organizations and agencies, regional organizations... to prevent,
combat and eliminate terrorism in all its forms and
manifestations," said a Interpol's statement. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990930.0126 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-30 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> National Day Celebration Nationwide </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 30 (Xinhua) -- Chinese people nationwide
today hosted a variety of activities to celebrate tomorrow's 50th
anniversary of the founding of the Peoples Republic of China (PRC).
</P>
<P>
More than 4,000 people attended a grand reception this morning
in Guangzhou, capital of south China's Guangdong Province, to
celebrate the great event.
</P>
<P>
Addressing the gathering, Lu Ruihua, governor of Guangdong,
said the province has witnessed tremendous development over the
past two decades of reform and opening-up.
</P>
<P>
People from various walks of life in Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous
Region, which neighbors Guangdong, gathered together at a big
party in the capital city of Nanning today to celebrate China's
National Day.
</P>
<P>
Cao Bochun, secretary of the regional CPC committee, called on
local people to make further efforts for the country's socialist
modernization construction under the leadership of the CPC Central
Committee with Jiang Zemin at the core and Deng Xiaoping Theory as
a guideline.
</P>
<P>
In Wuhan, capital of central China's Hubei Province, national
flags are flying in front of government departments, companies,
organizations and individual homes.
</P>
<P>
Southwest China's Tibet Autonomous Region also hosted a grand
National Day reception this evening, inviting 1,000 diplomats and
foreign experts, scholars and friends.  
