<HEADLINE> Bank Cards Gaining Popularity in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 30 (Xinhua) -- Nowadays, cash is not the
only means of payment for ordinary Chinese, as a variety of
plastic bank credit cards have appeared in many people's purses.
</P>
<P>
"Paying with a bank card is becoming a trend in China," said
Xiong Anping, general manager of Visa International Service
Association (VISA)'s China operations.
</P>
<P>
Over 20 Chinese commercial banks have issued credit cards, with
about 100 million now in circulation, Xiong said.
</P>
<P>
The total number of the cards is expected to reach 200 million
by the year 2003, he added.
</P>
<P>
The volume of bank cards issued has increased at an average
annual rate of 64 percent over the past five years, with the total
payments made with the cards rising by 76 percent annually.
</P>
<P>
However, still less than one percent of Chinese people pay with
bank credit card in their daily life.
</P>
<P>
Experts here say that bank cards will help stimulate domestic
demand.  
</P>
</TEXT>
