<HEADLINE> Nigerian Security Agents Arrest Abacha's Son </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, September 30 (Xinhua) -- Mohammed Abacha, the surviving
eldest son of Nigeria's late Head of State, General Sani Abacha,
was arrested Wednesday night in his hometown Kano by security
agents.
</P>
<P>
The Guardian, a leading Nigerian newspaper, Thursday quoted a
top presidential aide as saying that the arrest was not
unconnected with the imminent trial of Major Hamza Mustapha,
former Chief Security Officer to the late Gen. Abacha, and some
of his aides over the alleged murder of Alhaja Abiola, wife of the
acclaimed winner of the June 12 election, Chief M.K.O. Abiola.
</P>
<P>
It was still not clear where he was being held by security
agents believed to be acting on the orders of a team of police
investigators, said the paper.
</P>
<P>
An aide to Mustapha was reported in the current edition of The
News, a Lagos-based magazine, to have confessed to carrying out
the murder of the political activist on the orders of Mustapha.
</P>
<P>
A fortnight ago, Mohammed Abacha and his mother, Maryam, were
summoned to the capital for a meeting with Vice President Atiku
Abubaka over their refusal to cooperate with the new
administration's efforts to recover the state funds allegedly
looted and stashed away to foreign banks by late Gen. Abacha.
</P>
