<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shares Close Higher on Singapore Stock Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, September 30 (Xinhua) -- Share prices closed
slightly higher on the Singapore Stock Market Thursday with the
benchmark Straits Times Index (STI) earning 4.36 points to end at
2,021.93 in quiet trading.
</P>
<P>
Total turnover increased to 141.36 million units valued at
321.90 million Singapore dollars (188.25 million U.S. dollars).
Gainers outnumbered losers by 130 to 129 with 197 counters
unchanged.
</P>
<P>
Chuan H topped the volume chart with a turnover of 18.18
million shares. Gen Int came second with 12.87 million units done.
TiongWoon was the next with 6.21 million counters changing hands.
</P>
<P>
OCBC F led gainers of the day going up 40 cents to close at
13.20 Singapore dollars. OCBC and SIA gained 30 cents each to
finish at 12.50 and 16.60 Singapore dollars respectively.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, SPH headed the descent of the day with a loss
of 40 cents to close at 26.80 Singapore dollars. NatElec dropped
35 cents to finish at 26.35 Singapore dollars. DBS and Seaview
sank 30 cents to ended at 19.00 and 10.70 Singapore dollars
separately.
</P>
<P>
Dealers said the STI closed up on "window dressing" due to late
buying just before the market closed as some funds have to close
their accounts on a positive note.
</P>
<P>
Chuan Hup Holdings jumped 12.6 percent, or 17 cents to 1.52
Singapore dollars on news that the company's 1-for-5 split has
been approved by the Stock Exchange of Singapore. 
