<HEADLINE> Talks on Freeing Palestinian Prisoners Held </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GAZA, September 30 (Xinhua) -- Senior Palestinian and Israeli
officials on Thursday began their talks on the release of a third
batch of Palestinian prisoners from Israeli jails.
</P>
<P>
Palestinian Minister of State for Prisoners Affairs Hisham
Abdul Raziq met with Israeli Minister of Justice Yossi Beilin to
discuss the matter.
</P>
<P>
Raziq told reporters that in accordance with the Sharm
el-Sheikh Memorandum, approved by the Palestinian and Israeli
sides earlier this month, the third batch is to be released on
October 8.
</P>
<P>
The release will fall in the Islamic holy month of fasting,
Ramadan.
</P>
<P>
Raziq noted the third batch comprises 151 detainees, of whom 12
are from other Arab countries, adding that the Palestinian
Authority may host them in the Gaza strip should they opt to stay.
</P>
<P>
He said the present meeting with the Israeli sides aims at
working out technical details regard the release, not negotiating
the matter.
</P>
<P>
The Israeli side had freed 200 Palestinian detainees earlier
this month, in implementation of the Sharm el-Sheikh accord.
</P>
</TEXT>
