<HEADLINE> Hong Kong Stocks End Down </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, September 30 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong stocks dropped
101.65 points, or 0.79 percent, to end Thursday's session at 12,
733.24.
</P>
<P>
The turnover was 7.056 billion HK dollars ( 904 million U.S.
dollars), 152 million HK dollars (20 million U.S. dollars) lower
than Wednesday's turnover of 7.208 billion HK dollars (924 million
U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Traders attributed the changes to investors' inactiveness ahead
of a long weekend and next week's U.S. Federal Open Market
Committee meeting. Hong Kong is closed on Friday to mark China's
National Day.
</P>
<P>
Finance, Utilities, Properties and Commerce and Industry
suffered drops of 0.71 percent, 0.35 percent, 1.13 percent and 1.
15 percent, respectively.
</P>
<P>
China-related shares also ended lower with the Hang Seng China
Enterprises Index down 1.24 percent and the Hang Seng China-
Affiliated Corporations Index down 0.98 percent.
</P>
<P>
The Hang Seng Index dropped 36.21 points, or 0.28 percent, to
open at 12,798.68 Thursday and went down 8.37 points to finish
Thursday's morning session at 12,826.52.  
</P>
</TEXT>
