executive-designate of the Macao Special Administrative Region (
SAR), said Thursday that homes of the Macao people can only be
safeguarded by the motherland.
</P>
<P>
"Only the motherland can safeguard our homes. The resumption of
sovereignty over Macao by the motherland will make us have homes
which really belong to ourselves," Edmund Ho said in a written
message marking the 50 anniversary of the founding of the People's
Republic of China, which was released Thursday by his office.
</P>
<P>
He noted that over the past 50 years, the motherland has been
providing Macao with vital subsistence materials and giving
economic support to Macao. On the other hand, the Macao residents
have been generous to make donations when their compatriots in the
motherland suffer from difficulties.
</P>
<P>
"With the same root, the compatriots in the two areas have been
hold their hands tightly in the past 50 years," the future chief
executive said.
</P>
<P>
In the 50 years, the New China has managed to stand upright in
the world, winning independent sovereignty and basic reunification
of the country and entering a prosperous period by means of reform
and opening to outside world, he said.
</P>
<P>
"Acting as the chief executive, I will shoulder the
responsibility of creating a harmonious society which is able to
make steady progress," said Edmund Ho, who will be sworn into
office in less than three months.
</P>
<P>
"While we celebrate the 50th birthday of the our motherland, we
will strive to build a promising Macao in the future," he said in
his written message.  
</P>
