<HEADLINE> Malaysian Trade Mission to Visit Europe </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, September 30 (Xinhua) -- A Malaysian trade and
investment mission will visit Europe next month to enhance trade
links with European countries and promote investments into
Malaysia, the Ministry of International Trade and Industry
announced here Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The mission to be led by International Trade and Industry
Minister Rafidah Aziz will visit Germany, Belgium, Austria and
United Kingdom from October 2 to 13, the ministry said in a
statement.
</P>
<P>
The mission will update the European business community on
Malaysia's current economic situation as well as the trade and
investment opportunities in Malaysia.
</P>
<P>
The mission will seek investment joint-venture opportunities in
the information technology industry, security equipment and
services, the manufacture of hightech medical equipment and
pharmaceutical products, biotechnology, advance manufacturing
technology, advance communication, aerospace and automotive
sector, the statement said.
</P>
<P>
The mission will also seek export market opportunities for
timber- based products, CRT computer monitor, printed wired board,
specialized car accessories, home appliances, rubber gloves,
made-up garments, wire harness and printed circuit board,
pharmaceutical products, low carbon steel galvanized wire and
electronic and microelectronic security services, it said.
</P>
<P>
During the trip, Rafidah will address the local business
community at trade seminars to be held in Dusseldorf, Brussels,
Vienna and Manchester.
</P>
<P>
She will also attend the second ASEM (Asia-Europe Meeting)
Economic Ministers Meeting to be held in Berlin on October 9-10.
</P>
<P>
The delegation comprises central government officials,
representatives from the state governments of Johor, Pahang,
Kelantan and Sarawak and members from the private sector
representing 20 companies. 
