<HEADLINE> Jiang Enzhu Delivers National Day Message </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, September 30 (Xinhua) -- Jiang Enzhu, director of
the Xinhua News Agency Hong Kong Branch, said here Thursday that
the "one country, two systems" concept is a feasible and correct
principle of fulfilling China's reunification.
</P>
<P>
Extending greetings to Hong Kong residents on the eve of the
50th anniversary of the founding of the People's Republic of China,
Jiang reviewed China's achievements in economy, education,
national defense and diplomacy in the past five decades, and said
it is under such background that Hong Kong's return to the
motherland became historical certainty.
</P>
<P>
Jiang noted that Hong Kong remains to be an international
financial, trade and shipping center as well as a free port after
it returned to the motherland.
</P>
<P>
Its former social and economic systems and its lifestyle all
remain unchanged, he said, and the rights and freedom of Hong Kong
people prescribed in the Basic Law are fully guaranteed.
</P>
<P>
The central government has been always firmly carrying out the
principles of the "one country, two systems," "Hong Kong people
administering Hong Kong," and a high-degree of autonomy in Hong
Kong, he stressed.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the central government has offered full support to
the SAR administration headed by Chief Executive Tung Chee Hwa in
accordance with the Basic Law, and has maintained the prosperity
and stability of the region, he said.
</P>
<P>
He pointed out that Hong Kong's economic difficulty has now
bottomed out, and that the region has get out of the negative
economic growth in the second quarter of this year.
</P>
<P>
Facts demonstrate that the SAR government has exerted the right
governance over Hong Kong and is capable of administering the Hong
Kong society and managing complicated situations, he said.
</P>
<P>
Reiterating the principle of "peaceful reunification, and one
country, two systems" in solving the Taiwan issue, Jiang stressed
that the Chinese government and people will never allow separation
of the territory and state sovereignty.
</P>
<P>
With the concerted efforts of the Chinese people at home and
overseas, he believed that the complete reunification of the
motherland and the overall invigoration of the Chinese nation will
surely come true.
</P>
<P>
Jiang also expressed his concern and sympathy to the Taiwan
compatriots in connection with the strong earthquake, which
occurred in Taiwan not long ago.  
</P>
</TEXT>
