<DOCNO> XIE19990930.0176 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-30 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> EU Offers Aid for Sierra Leone, Russia, Yemen </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, September 30 (Xinhua) -- The European Commission has
approved humanitarian aid totaling 7.3 million euros (7.6 million
U.S. dollars) for Sierra Leone, Russia and Yemen.
</P>
<P>
The aid, administered by the Commission's Humanitarian Office,
will enable non-governmental organizations and international
humanitarian organizations to carry out a variety of projects over
the next 10 months.
</P>
<P>
The European Union executive body said it will provide 5
million euros (5.25 million dollars) worth of aid for refugees and
people at risk in Sierra Leone, where the humanitarian situation
is worrying.
</P>
<P>
This comprehensive emergency aid plan includes health,
nutrition, drinking water and hygiene for the population of Sierra
Leone and refugees from Guinea and Liberia.
</P>
<P>
The EU will also provide AN aid of 1.8 million euros (1.89
million dollars) for tuberculosis sufferers in Russia.
</P>
<P>
The funds will enable the Danish and British Red Cross to
distribute regular hot meals, food and hygiene kits, to train home
nurses and reequip health centers, in addition to supplying the
purely medical aid.
</P>
<P>
The aid of 500,000 euros (525,000 dollars) for Yemen will go to
help vulnerable groups such as Somali refugees and repatriated
Yemeni workers who are living in extreme hardship.
</P>
<P>
"The aid will consist mainly of health supplies, basic
equipment, training of health workers and assistance with economic
integration for repatriated workers," the EU Commission said in a
statement. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
