<HEADLINE> PRC Founding Anniversary Photo Show Ends in Myanmar </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, September 30 (Xinhua) -- The photo and film exhibition
marking the 50th anniversary of the founding of the People's
Republic of China ended at the National Museum here Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The exhibition, jointly sponsored by the Chinese embassy and
the Myanmar Ministry of Culture, displayed 105 sheets of photos,
which reflected the earth-shaking change of China in 20 years
since it adopted the reform and opening up policy.
In addition, 10 Chinese feature films were also shown.
</P>
<P>
Viewed with full of zeal the exhibition were officials of
Myanmar government ministries, invited friendly guests from
different walks of life, Myanmar-Chinese and Chinese residents,
and foreign diplomats in Myanmar totaling over 10,000.
</P>
<P>
The week-long exhibition began on September 24. 
