<HEADLINE> Zhu Reviews PRC's Achievements in Past 50 Years </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 30 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Premier Zhu Rongji
said today that the enormous achievements the Chinese people have
scored in the 50 years since the founding of new China have gone
down as the most brilliant chapters in the annals of the Chinese
nation.
</P>
<P>
Zhu made the remarks at a reception marking the 50th
anniversary of the founding of the People's Republic of China held
at the Great Hall of the People this evening.
</P>
<P>
"These achievements should be attributed to the great, glorious
and correct Communist Party of China, to the hard-working, brave
and talented people of China and to the superior socialist system,
" he stressed.
</P>
<P>
He said that the founding of the People's Republic of China 50
years ago opened up a new epoch in the history of China. "Over
these five decades, under the leadership of the Communist Party of
China, people of all ethnic groups in China, working hard in unity
and forging ahead in face of all odds and difficulties, have
brought earth-shaking transformations to the face of our country,"
he stated.
</P>
<P>
He mentioned the two decades since the introduction of the
reform and opening-up policy in particular, saying that China, by
Deng Xiaoping Theory and the basic Party line, has made great and
remarkable achievements in its socialist modernization and
significant progress in the economic restructuring.
</P>
<P>
"Our national economy has been growing in a sustained, rapid,
and healthy way and all undertakings ranging from science and
technology to education and culture are moving ahead in full swing.
Our people's life has bettered markedly. Socialist democracy and
legal system have continued to improve. The unity of all ethnic
groups has been further consolidated," he pointed out.
</P>
<P>
The premier said that "Our great country which is thriving and
growing with each passing day has stood rock firm in the east of
the world."
</P>
<P>
On the country's diplomacy in the past five decades, he said
that "We have enjoyed an ever rising international standing and we
have friends all over the world."
</P>
<P>
According to Zhu, China over the past five decades has never
wavered in pursuing an independent foreign policy of peace and
safeguarding state sovereignty, territorial integrity and national
dignity and has stood the severe tests of changes in the
international situation.
</P>
<P>
"We have established diplomatic relations with more than 160
countries and maintained economic and cultural exchanges with
other countries and regions in the world," he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
