<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-30 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Premier: China's Economy Maintains Sound Development Momentum </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 30 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Premier Zhu Rongji
said today that China's national economy has continued to maintain
a sound momentum of development since the beginning of this year.
</P>
<P>
Zhu made the remarks at a reception marking the 50th
anniversary of the founding of the People Republic of China held
at the Great Hall of the People this evening.
</P>
<P>
According to the premier, "Faced with the complex international
and domestic environment, the CPC Central Committee and the State
Council have taken a full stock of the difficulties that might
arise and come up with a correct and comprehensive response in a
timely and decisive manner."
</P>
<P>
Intensifying the implementation of a pro-active fiscal policy,
he said, "we have worked to increase investment, stimulate
consumption, accelerate structural readjustment and technological
innovation, and expand export", adding that these measures have
exerted a positive impact on the national economy.
</P>
<P>
"The agricultural sector has been reinforced and a bumper
harvest has again been obtained for the summer crops. Industrial
production has been growing steadily with economic returns
markedly recovered. State revenue is growing fairly fast and the
financial sector is running smoothly. Progress has been made in
the reform of state-owned enterprises (SOE). People's living
standards have seen new highs," he said.
</P>
<P>
He stressed that "the just concluded Fourth Plenary Session of
the 15th CPC Central Committee adopted the Decision by the CPC
Central Committee on Several Major Issues Concerning the Reform
and Development of SOEs, which is a programmatic document guiding
the reform and development of China's SOEs.
</P>
<P>
He said that "we must faithfully implement the spirit of the
Decision and work in a down-to-earth manner and with full
confidence to usher in a new situation in the reform and
development of China's SOEs, which will facilitate the development
of the entire national economy."
</P>
<P>
Zhu pointed out that "historical experience shows us that
nothing can be accomplished without stability. We should value all
the more dearly the hard-won situation of unity and stability and
properly manage the interaction among reform, development and
stability."
</P>
<P>
"While correctly handling the internal contradictions among the
people under the new circumstances, we should, in the meantime,
firmly crack down on all law-breaking criminal activities to
safeguard social stability and state security and ensure smooth
progress in the reform, opening-up and modernization drive," he
said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
