<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-30 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Macao's Return One More Major Step Toward China's Reunification, Premier Zhu </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 30 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Premier Zhu Rongji
here today said that Macao's return to the motherland will mark
one more major step forward in the Chinese people's great cause of
peaceful reunification of the country and another historic event
for the Chinese nation.
</P>
<P>
While addressing a reception marking the 50th anniversary of
the founding of the People's Republic of China, the premier said
that "China will resume the exercise of sovereignty over Macao as
of 20 December this year. At present, preparations for Macao's
return are moving ahead in an orderly way and a smooth transition
and transfer of government in Macao will be realized."
</P>
<P>
He stated that "the Chinese Government will unswervingly
implement the policies of 'one country, two systems', 'Hong Kong
people administering Hong Kong', 'Macao people administering
Macao' and a high degree of autonomy."
</P>
<P>
"Facts have proved that our compatriots in Hong Kong have the
full capacity to run Hong Kong well and facts will also prove that
our Macao compatriots will surely have the capacity to manage the
future Macao Special Administrative Region well," he pointed out.
</P>
<P>
"The Central Government and the mainland will forever be a
powerful backing for Hong Kong and Macao in their effort to
maintain lasting prosperity and stability. With joint efforts from
people of all circles in the two regions, Hong Kong and Macao will
exhibit even more brilliance and vitality," he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990930.0191 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-30 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Zhu: Complete Reunification of China Will Be Realized </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 30 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Premier Zhu Rongji
said today that "we are convinced that with concerted efforts of
the entire Chinese people, the Taiwan question will be resolved at
an early date following the return of Hong Kong and Macao and the
complete reunification of China will be realized."
</P>
<P>
He made the remarks at a reception marking the 50 anniversary
of the founding of the People's Republic of China held at the
Great Hall of the People here this evening.
</P>
<P>
"To resolve the Taiwan question and realize the complete
reunification of the motherland is the lofty aspiration and sacred
mission of the entire Chinese people, including Taiwan compatriots,
" he said.
</P>
<P>
He stressed that "over the past 50 years, the CPC, the Chinese
Government and people have fought a long and unremitting struggle
for that, which has helped firmly safeguard the status of Taiwan
as part of Chinese territory and vigorously promoted economic,
cultural and personnel exchanges across the Taiwan Straits.
</P>
<P>
"Currently, we are engaged in a campaign against Lee Teng-hui's
'two states theory' and for the state sovereignty and territorial
integrity. This is in full accord with the fundamental interests
of the Chinese nation," he said.
</P>
<P>
On Taiwan's recent strong earthquake, Zhu said that "we are
very much concerned about this big disaster. We have expressed our
deep sympathy to our compatriots in Taiwan and we stand ready to
continue to render assistance and aid to them as far as we can."
</P>
<P>
He said that "we will continue to pursue the basic policy of
'peaceful reunification, and one country, two systems" and
President Jiang Zemin's eight-point proposal on the development of
the cross-Straits relations and the advancement of the process of
peaceful reunification of the motherland." 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
