<DOCNO> XIE19990930.0192 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-30 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Premier on China's Foreign Policy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 30 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Premier Zhu Rongji
said here today that "The Chinese people will work together with
people of other countries for a lasting peace in the world and
common prosperity of all humanity and make due contribution to
that."
</P>
<P>
He made the remarks at a reception marking the 50th anniversary
of the founding of the People's Republic of China held at the
Great Hall of the People this evening.
</P>
<P>
"The current international situation is on the whole moving
toward relaxation, though instances of local turmoil have cropped
up one after another," he said.
</P>
<P>
"The Chinese Government will continue to follow an independent
foreign policy of peace and resolutely oppose hegemonism and power
politics. We will actively develop friendly relations and
cooperation with other countries in the world on the basis of the
Five Principles of Peaceful Coexistence and vigorously promote
exchanges and cooperation with them in various fields on the basis
of equality and mutual benefit," he reiterated. 
</P>
</TEXT>
