<HEADLINE> Expressway on West Bank of Taiwan Straits Taking Shape(2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
Facing Taiwan across the Straits, Fujian has made use of its
prime location and improved its economy since 1980.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that over the past five years, the province's
gross national product (GDP) has increased by 17.9 percent
annually on average, ranking between 12th and 15th in the country.
</P>
<P>
"In addition to ocean shipping, the province has to rely on
the inefficient Xiamen-Yingtan railway and many low-quality
highways, which cannot meet the demand of Fujian's rapidly-
increasing economy," Chen pointed out.
</P>
<P>
Zhou Chunming, director of Fuzhou's transportation bureau,
noted that the modern expressways will help to cut back on travel
time. 
