<DOCNO> XIE19990930.0197 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-30 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Vietnam Makes A New Effort to Boost Exports </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, September 30 (Xinhua) -- The Vietnamese government is
making a new effort to boost its exports by deciding to establish
the Export Supporting Fund, the Vietnam News Agency reported
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Vietnamese Prime Minister Phan Van Khai issued last Monday a
decision on the establishment, use and management of the Export
Supporting Fund in order to boost exports, expand outlets for and
increase the competitiveness of Vietnam's exports.
</P>
<P>
The fund, which is to be managed by the Finance Ministry, will
be used to support the purchase of farm produce for export under
the government's control, and provide financial assistance for
some kinds of export goods that suffer losses in certain periods,
and give rewards to encourage the expansion of foreign outlets and
production of new export goods.
</P>
<P>
The fund's capital will be raised from seven sources, namely,
earnings from differences in prices of export and import goods,
the annual supplementary allocation from the State budget, the
collection of import and export quota granting fees, goods origin
certificate granting fees, charges on the issuance of licenses for
representative offices and branches of international organizations
and foreign companies to operate in Vietnam, contributions from
exporters and money collected from other sources in accordance
with the decision.
</P>
<P>
The Finance Ministry is assigned to coordinate with the Trade
Ministry, the Government's Price Committee and concerned agencies
to issue guidelines on the management and use of the fund in
accordance with the decision.
</P>
<P>
The decision will take effect 15 days after being signed.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
