<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Unemployment Rate in France Up in August </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, September 30 (Xinhua) -- The number of jobless people in
France increased by 8,400, or 0.3 percent, in August compared with
July, said the Ministry of Employment on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The number of jobless people in France stood at 2,778,800 and
the unemployment rate 11.3 percent by the end of August.
</P>
<P>
The government said the jobless rate rise last month is a
normal phenomenon, because the term of many "small jobs" in the
summer vacation time expired at the end of July.
</P>
<P>
The rise was a disruption of an all-time dropping of
unemployment rate in the country, since the rate has kept dropping
each month since July 1997, except in July and August 1998.
</P>
</TEXT>
