<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, September 30 (Xinhua) -- French police arrested three
Basque separatists Thursday morning and seized 1.9 tons of
explosives from them, reported Agence France-Presse.
</P>
<P>
Police broke into a villa house in the Pyrennees-Atlantiques
region in southwest France near the Spanish border and arrested
two men and one woman suspected to be members of the Spanish
Basque separatist group ETA.
</P>
<P>
