<HEADLINE> Grand Flag-Hoisting Ceremony for PRC 50th Anniversary Scheduled </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 30 (Xinhua) -- A grand flag-hoisting
ceremony will be held at the Tian'anmen Square at about 10:00 a.m.
tomorrow to celebrate the 50th anniversary of the founding of the
People's Republic of China (PRC).
</P>
<P>
Jia Qinglin, member of the Political Bureau of the Communist
Party of China (CPC) Central Committee, and secretary of the
Beijing Municipal Committee of the CPC will announce on the
Tian'anmen Rostrum the start of the celebrations of the 50th
anniversary of the founding of the PRC.
</P>
<P>
Amid a 50-gun salute, a national flag guarding contingent
consisting of 200 armed police soldiers in uniforms will walk down
the platform of the Monument to the People's Heroes in the
southern part of the Tian'anmen Square, and march northerly on a
10-meter-wide red carpet spread along the north-south axial line
of the square towards the national flag post. A soldier will raise
the national flag by pressing a button.
</P>
<P>
Chinese leaders, representatives of people from all walks of
life on the Tian'anmen Rostrum, and tens of thousands of people at
the square will watch the ceremony.
</P>
<P>
The Tian'anmen Square has an area of 50 hectares and is
believed to be the largest city square in the world. Fifty years
ago, the founding ceremony of the People's Republic of China was
held in the square and the late Chairman Mao Zedong announced the
birth of New China. Mao pressed the button to hoist the first
national flag of New China. 
</P>
</TEXT>
