<HEADLINE> China's Military Being Equipped with Hi-tech Weapons </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 30 (Xinhua) -- China has been increasing its
defense strength with more advanced weapons technology in recent
years, according to a PLA General Armaments Department official.
</P>
<P>
Less than 10 years after the People's Republic of China was
founded in 1949, the country was able to manufacture conventional
weapons like tanks and artillery.
</P>
<P>
Since the mid-1960s, China has developed the atomic bomb, the H-
bomb, neutron bomb, missiles with various ranges, nuclear
submarines, and military satellites, making it one of a few
countries developing sophisticated weapons by itself.
</P>
<P>
The official says that the Chinese government has always placed
a great deal of importance on research and development of new
weapons, even though defense still occupies a relatively small
part of the national budget.
</P>
<P>
The official says that it has an array of new types of tanks
and anti-tank weapons, guided missile destroyers, fighters, and
long-range missiles and has had breakthroughs in electronics
research, miniaturization of nuclear weapons, missile guidance
technology, and laser weapons. 
</P>
</TEXT>
