<HEADLINE> Taiwan Receives Donation From China's Mainland </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Beijing, September 30 (Xinhua) -- The Taiwan Red Cross Society
has received a donation of 99,985 U.S. dollars from the mainland
of China, the Red Cross Society of China announced yesterday.
</P>
<P>
The original 100,000 U.S. dollar donation of the mainland was
transferred by the Bank of China to a Hong Kong bank, which in
turn transferred the money to an American bank. The American bank
deducted a 15-dollar commission, explained Sun Aiming, secretary
general of the society.
</P>
<P>
"Donations from all the provinces will be converted into US
dollars and be remitted to Taiwan. We have told the bank to notify
us if there are any commission fees," he said, adding that the
society would pay the commission fees.
</P>
<P>
China's Red Cross Society organized a rescue team soon after
the massive earthquake hit Taiwan on September 21. Its members are
prepared to go to Taiwan without delay as soon as they receive
permission from Taiwan.  
</P>
