<HEADLINE> Over Half of Zambians Drink Contaminated Water: </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, September 30 (Xinhua) -- At least 54 percent of the
Zambians are consuming contaminated water from shallow wells, a
senior Zambian health official said.
</P>
<P>
Gavin Silwamba, Director General of the Zambian Central Board
of Health, said a study revealed that 90 percent of water of the
shallow wells is contaminated, according to the Times of Zambia
newspaper report on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Human waste filtered from the toilets into the water and many
children died of diarrhoea, he added.
</P>
<P>
"For every 1,000 births, 100 die of diarrhoea or diseases
related to bad water," the health official said. 
</P>
