<DOCNO> XIE19990930.0245 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-30 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Backgrounder: History Of People's Republic Of China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 30 (Xinhua) -- The People's Republic of
China was founded on October 1, 1949, with Beijing as its capital.
</P>
<P>
It is one of the four municipalities that are directly under
Central Government jurisdiction. It is China's political,
scientific, cultural, and international exchange center.
</P>
<P>
The national flag with five stars on a red background was
designed in 1949 by Zeng Liansong, a clerk in Shanghai. The five-
point yellow stars are in the upper left-hand corner, with four
smaller yellow stars forming a crescent next to the larger one.
</P>
<P>
The national emblem is composed of the national flag,
Tian'anmen, gears, and ears of wheat and rice.
</P>
<P>
The red symbolizes revolution. The larger star represents the
Communist Party of China (CPC) and the four smaller ones stand for
the Chinese people. Together they represent the unity of the
Chinese people under the leadership of the CPC.
</P>
<P>
The national anthem was originally called "March of the
Volunteers". It was from the film "Zhonghua Ernu" or "Chinese
Young Heroes and Heroines in Stormy Years" and was written in 1935,
with lyrics by Tian Han, a famous poet, and music by Nie Er, a
famous composer.
</P>
<P>
The People's Republic of China includes the mainland and
islands along the coast, Taiwan and its islands, the Penghu
archipelago, Dongsha archipelago, Xisha archipelago, Zhongsha
archipelago, Nansha archipelago, and all other islands which
belong to the People's Republic of China. The width of China's
territory waters is 12 nautical miles beginning from the basic
line of the territory waters and the width of China's adjacent
area is 24 nautical miles.
</P>
<P>
The PRC is in the eastern part of Asia on the Pacific Ocean.
The northernmost point is the midway point of the Heilongjiang
River and the southernmost is Zhengmu Reef of the Nansha
Archipelago. The westernmost point is the Pamirs and the
easternmost, the confluence of Heilongjiang and Wusulijiang rivers.
</P>
<P>
There are 56 nationalities in China, with the Han accounting
for 93.3 per cent of the total. The ethnic groups mainly inhabit
northwest, southwest and northeast parts of the country.
</P>
<P>
The country has 23 provinces, 5 autonomous regions, 4
municipalities, and the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region.
The Macao Special Administrative Region will be established
according to law when Macao returns to the motherland this
December.  At the end of 1998, China had a population of more
than 1.24 billion. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990930.0246 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-30 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Backgrounder: History Of Beijing's Great Hall Of People </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
It was built in ten months in 1959, with 171,800 sq. m. of
floor space, an area larger than the total area of the Forbidden
City just across east-west Chang'an Avenue. It has been an
important site of political and foreign affairs and is the meeting
place of the National People's Congress (NPC), China's top
legislature, and its Standing Committee.
</P>
<P>
The main entrance faces the square to the east and is flanked
by twelve 25-m.-tall light-grey marble columns and has a large
national emblem above the lintel.
</P>
<P>
The central hall is just inside the entrance, with a 76m. x 60m.
conference hall that can seat 10,000 people. On the north side of
the hall is a banquet hall that can seat 5,000 people. The
southern wing holds offices of the NPC Standing Committee.
</P>
<P>
The Hall also has smaller halls named after China's provinces,
municipalities and autonomous regions, decorated in local styles.
</P>
<P>
The Hall was designed by Zhao Dongri and Shen Qi, the chief
architects of the Beijing Architectural Design Institute, in a
combination of classical European style and traditional Chinese
methods for its interior and exterior.
</P>
<P>
To prepare for China's 50th founding anniversary celebrations,
the Beijing government had a large-scale renovation of the hall
and 50,000 sq.m. of the building's exterior was refaced with
granite, while the glazed tile used in parts of the hall has been
changed.
</P>
<P>
After China adopted the policy of reform and opening-up, the
hall was opened to the public. Thousands of tourists visit the
Great Hall of the People every day.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990930.0247 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-30 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Backgrounder: History Of Beijing's Tian'anmen Square </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 30 (Xinhua)-- Tomorrow will be the 50
anniversary of the People's Republic of China and several hundred
thousand people are expected to converge on the world's largest
city square, Beijing's Tian'anmen Square, to celebrate the special
day.
</P>
<P>
The square is in the center of Beijing. The site was originally
a courtyard of the Imperial Palace. The nearby area was used for
government buildings in the Ming and Qing dynasties, with Zhonghua
Gate to the south, Chang'an Left Gate to the southeast and
Chang'an Right Gate to the southwest.
</P>
<P>
During those two dynasties, ordinary people were not allowed
into the yard and even members of the nobility could not enter it
freely. The emperors of the Ming and Qing used Tian'anmen as the
entrance and exit point for their annual ritual activities
involving heaven and the ancestors. Whenever the emperor was
beginning a military action, he would hold a ceremony in front of
Tian'anmen to pray for the safe return of those involved.
</P>
<P>
In addition, Tian'anmen was used by the emperor to summon
successful candidates in the highest imperial examinations.
</P>
<P>
Since the founding of the People's Republic of China, the
Tian'anmen Square has been a center of political activities and
many other important activities. People regard it as the heart of
the nation. Early in the morning, tens of thousands of people
gather there to watch the flag-raising ceremony. The ceremony on
August 1, 1997 attracted a record 200,000 people.
</P>
<P>
The square has undergone a series of renovations and expansions
and it is now surrounded by the rostrum, Monument to the People's
Heroes, Memorial Hall of Chairman Mao, Museum of Chinese History,
Museum of the Chinese Revolution, and the Great Hall of the People.
</P>
<P>
From last October to this June, the government of Beijing
refurbished the square. The renovation work included paving it
with pink granite, improving the lighting and audio system, adding
more grass, and updating the fountain system, leaving an 880-m. by
500-m. square. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990930.0248 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-30 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Backgrounder: History Of Beijing's Chang'an Avenue </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 30 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese often say that
anyone who has not been to the Great Wall is not a true man, but,
in the case of Beijing, if you haven't strolled down Chang'an
Avenue, you may regret it when you get back home.
</P>
<P>
The avenue has a history of more than 700 years and evolved
from Suncheng Street in Dadu, the capital of the Yuan Dynasty (
1271-1368). By the Ming Dynasty (1368-1644), it was still only a
narrow yellow dust road and even when it had cobblestones added at
the end of the Qing Dynasty (1644-1911), it was an encircled and
forbidden area until the Revolution of 1911.
</P>
<P>
Since the founding of New China, it has had several renovations.
The two sections, Xidan to Fuxinmen, and Dongdan to Jianguomen,
were eastward and westward expansions in the 1950s for the
convenience of traffic. The two sections were widened to as much
as 100 meters, from the 12 meters of the early years of New China.
</P>
<P>
Chang'an starts from Shijingshan in the west and runs to the
Tongzhou District 42 kilometers to the east, giving it the name "
First Street of China". But, the real Chang'an Avenue only runs
from Xidan to Dongdan, for 6.7 kilometers, which is why it is
often referred to as "the 10-li Long Street" (1 li is half a
kilometer).
</P>
<P>
The name Chang'an (or 'eternal peace') came from the name of
the capital of the prosperous Tang Dynasty and meant long-lasting
government and stability.
</P>
<P>
It has been the scene of many shocking events, but many
important government departments and organizations are located
along it, like Zhongnanhai, the Great Hall of the People, the
Ministry of Public Security, the Ministry of State Security, the
Ministry of Foreign Trade and Economic Cooperation, the Ministry
of Railways, the Ministry of Communications, the People's Bank of
China, and the All-China Women's Federation.
</P>
<P>
In preparation for the 50th anniversary of New China, the city
government of Beijing had carried out a large-scale renovation
project on Chang'an, from Gongzhufen to Dabeiyao, which included
cleaning up areas in front of buildings, sidewalk reconstruction
work, repairing intersections and lighting, and demolishing
signboards, giving it back its solemn and dignified style and
putting as lot more green areas along it.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990930.0249 </DOCNO>
