<HEADLINE> Chinese Youngsters to Plant Trees For 'Mother River' </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 30 (Xinhua) -- China will get children and
youngsters involved in a tree-planting drive in the city of Jiyuan
in central Henan Province to improve the environment of the Yellow
River.
</P>
<P>
The project, the first of its kind, is expected to cover more
than 330 hectares of land scattered on mountainsides near the
Xiaolangdi Reservoir on this 'mother river', according to a
National Committee for Youth official.
</P>
<P>
The committee is sponsoring the drive and will ask children and
youngsters to donate their time and energy to the tree planting in
the region.
</P>
<P>
The wooded area could become a major man-made forest and
ecological tourist attraction, the official says.  
</P>
</TEXT>
