<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Bangladeshi PM to Visit Australia in October </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, September 30 (Xinhua) -- Bangladeshi Prime Minister
Sheikh Hasina will pay a three-day official visit to Australia on
October 20-22, The Daily Star newspaper reported Thursday.
</P>
<P>
This will be the first visit by a Bangladeshi head of state or
government to Australia, an important development partner of
Bangladesh and one of the country's donors.
</P>
<P>
The prime minister will hold official talks with her Australian
counterpart John Howard in Canberra and will also visit Sydney and
Melbourne.
</P>
<P>
Hasina is likely to seek increased Australian investment in
Bangladesh and address an investors' conference there.
Bangladeshi-Australian trade is "insignificant" now, and the trip
is expected to increase bilateral trade, concerned sources were
quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the prime minister will fly to South Africa on
November 10 to attend the Commonwealth Heads of Government Meeting
in Durban on November 12-15, and will attend the 11th SAARC (South
Asian Association for Regional Cooperation) Summit in Kathmandu on
November 26-28.
</P>
<P>
Bangladesh is contesting for the post of Commonwealth secretary
general, which will be elected during the summit in South Africa,
and the 11th SAARC summit is expected to adopt a "binding treaty"
specifying a time frame for creating a South Asian Free Trade
Area, according to the report. 
</P>
</TEXT>
