<HEADLINE> Bangladesh to Establish Special Force to Combat Crimes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, September 30 (Xinhua) -- The government of Bangladesh
has recently taken a decision to establish a special force with
the aim at tracking down criminals and thus uprooting crimes from
society.
</P>
<P>
Taking part in the country's emergency needs, particularly
during the natural calamities, will also be among the assignments
of the new police force, the local weekly magazine Dhaka Courier
reported Thursday in its latest issue.
</P>
<P>
The report quoted Inspector General of Police A.Y.B.I. Siddiqui
as saying that the force would not be used for any political
purposes or gaining personal interests by any quarter.
</P>
<P>
As a matter of fact there is no commando team in Bangladesh's
police force, so, they frequently fall prey to many embarrassing
situation, Siddiqui said adding this rapid-action team is being
formed on directive of the home minister.
</P>
<P>
The report said the commando force of police will conduct quick
raids in any emergency situation. It is the part of the
government's latest effort to track down criminals and root out
terrorism. The storm-trooper corps will be given all kinds of
rescue training and be well equipped so that they can face any
situation.
</P>
<P>
The police commandos would be selected from the armed police
battalion. There are 9 battalions of armed police in the country.
One platoon of police will be selected from each battalion for
special training. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
