<HEADLINE> Myanmar Establishes Diplomatic Ties With Tajikistan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, September 30 (Xinhua) -- Myanmar established diplomatic
relations with Tajikistan Wednesday at the ambassadorial level,
according to a press communique issued by the Myanmar Foreign
Ministry Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Tajikistan is the 84th country in the world with which Myanmar
has established diplomatic ties since its independence in 1948.
</P>
<P>
It is also the 8th country with which Myanmar forged links this
year. The prior seven countries are Ukraine, Azerbaijan, Georgia,
Turkmenistan, Croatia, Belarus and Kazakhstan.
</P>
<P>
Myanmar has opened 29 embassies, two permanent missions and two
consulates-general in various parts of the world, according to the
ministry. 
</P>
</TEXT>
