<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Private Banks in Myanmar to Extend Industrial Loans </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, September 30 (Xinhua) -- Private banks in Myanmar will
collectively and individually disburse loans to local
entrepreneurs of industrial zones and agricultural projects
beginning October 1, official newspaper The New Light of Myanmar
reported Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Aimed at developing industries and agricultural enterprises in
the country, Myanmar Banks Association and Industrial and
Agricultural Loans Advisory and Supervisory Committee are making
arrangements to disburse the loans under the guidelines of the
government.
</P>
<P>
Interest rate for the loans is 15 percent, the report said.
</P>
<P>
Since the beginning of this year, the Myanmar government has
urged private banks in the country to extend loans to
entrepreneurs establishing industrial zones and reclaiming vacant,
virgin and fallow lands for cultivation.
</P>
<P>
In response to the government's call, private banks in the
country have opened more and more branches in regions where
industrial zones are set up and lands reclaimed.
</P>
<P>
There are 19 private banks in Myanmar with a total of over 60
branches throughout the country.
</P>
<P>
The private banks in Myanmar hold about 45 percent of saving
deposits of the banking sector, while their loans account for
about 48 percent of the sector's loans to the private sector.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
