<DOCNO> XIE19990930.0280 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-30 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Strong China Serves World Peace, Development: Cambodian FM </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PHNOM PENH, September 30 (Xinhua) -- A strong China will be in
the interests of the peace, stability and development of Asia and
the whole world, Cambodian Foreign Minister Hor Nam Hong said in a
recent interview with Xinhua.
</P>
<P>
"Great changes have taken place since new China was founded in
1949, especially during the past two decades of reform and opening-
up initiated by late senior Chinese leader Deng Xiaoping," Nor Nam
Hong said on the occasion of the 50th anniversary of the founding
of the People's Republic of China, which falls on October 1.
</P>
<P>
Hor Nam Hong, who as a senior diplomat has been to China
several times and visited many Chinese cities, said, "What strikes
me most is the remarkable improvement of the people's living
standards and that the 1.2 billion population has enough to eat."
</P>
<P>
Besides, the increase in "the country's overall strength has
also greatly impressed" him, according to the foreign minister.
</P>
<P>
Refuting the so-called "China threat" fallacy spread by a few
countries, Nor spoke highly of China's foreign policy of pursuing
the principle of respect for the independence and sovereignty of
other nations.
</P>
<P>
"China, as a permanent member of the United Nations Security
Council, has always voiced and represented the interests and
aspirations of the developing countries," he said.
</P>
<P>
Hor reiterated Cambodia's one-China policy, which treats Taiwan
only as a province of China. He also praised China's "one country,
two systems" policy.
</P>
<P>
He thanked the Chinese government for its consistent assistance
to Cambodia and said that friendly and cooperative relations
between Cambodia and China not only serve the common interests of
both countries and their peoples, but also the peace and
development of Asia and the world.
</P>
<P>
He likened the friendship between Cambodia and China to "a
large edifice with a solid foundation" laid down by the old
generations of leaders in both countries.
</P>
<P>
Hor expressed his firm belief that in the next century, the
friendly and cooperative relations between the two countries will
be further strengthened and broadened, and China will become a
great economic power under the Chinese leadership with President
Jiang Zemin at the core. 
</P>
</TEXT>
