<HEADLINE> Film Studio Influences People's Daily Life </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGCHUN, September 30 (Xinhua) -- The Changchun Film Studio
in China's Jilin Province has made quite a few well-known films
since 1945 and has had an influence on several generations of
people.
</P>
<P>
The 280,000-sq.m. studio has a white marble statue of Mao
Zedong in front of its main three-story building which was built
in the 1930s.
</P>
<P>
Zhao Guoguang, head of the studio, says that China's first
documentary, puppetoon, dubbed films, and science and educational
films all came out of the studio. The heroes and heroines in "
Offspring of Heroes", "Dong Cunrui", "The Opium War", which were
made in the 17 years before the chaotic Cultural Revolution in
1966, provided quite a few models for the Chinese at that time.
</P>
<P>
The studio, a major one in the country, has reformed some of
its operations since last year and its technology is expected to
catch up with the rest of the world when hi-tech equipment is
installed at the end of this year. The studio will put its films
on the international market one day, Zhao says.
</P>
<P>
It has produced over 600 films over the past 50 years, dubbed
more than 800 foreign films, and won 70 awards in China and abroad,
in addition to having trained over 1,000 outstanding actors,
actresses, and technicians. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
