<BODY>
<HEADLINE> All Sri Lankan Teachers to Be Trained by Year 2002 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, September 30 (Xinhua) -- The Sri Lankan government has
planned to complete the training of all teachers in the country
now in service before year 2002 and no appointments will be given
to untrained teachers thereafter, media sources said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The teachers will be provided month's training at the country's
14 existing educational faculties and five other such faculties
which will soon be established, the sources said.
</P>
<P>
At present, untrained graduate teachers are undergoing training
at education faculties in Colombo, Peradeniya and Jaffna. In
addition to these educational faculties, the National Institute of
Education and the Open Universities will also provide teacher
training programs to untrained graduate teachers, Education and
High Education Ministry officials said.
</P>
<P>
They added that some teachers had never received any training
during their entire careers. It was essential to provide an
in-house training for untrained teachers. 
</P>
