<HEADLINE> Northeastern Chinese Province Has 70 Centenarians </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGCHUN, September 30 (Xinhua) -- A four-month study has
revealed that there are more than 2 million people above the age
of 60 in China's Jilin Province and that 70 are centenarians.
</P>
<P>
The province has over 26 million people. The provincial
government has given the 70 elderly the title "Senior Citizens of
the Century" and has selected nine of them for "Longevity Stars".
</P>
<P>
The selection was based on the state of their health and their
contributions to the country. Bai Zhaoshi, the oldest, is 112 and
a couple, Wang Lanzhou and Wang Guoshi, are both 103. At an awards
ceremony, 103-year-old Li Hushi attributed her longevity to
exercise and the better life today in the New China. 
</P>
</TEXT>
