<HEADLINE> Liverpool Waits on Fowler Decision </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, September 29 (Xinhua) -- English premier league
football club Liverpool have delayed a decision on whether striker
Robbie Fowler requires surgery that could put him out for six
weeks.
</P>
<P>
Boss Gerard Houllier discussed Fowler's worrying ankle problem
with his medical staff on Wednesday and it was decided that the
England hitman should continue with intensive treatment until the
end of the week.
</P>
<P>
Liverpool are desperate not to be forced into a decision that
will rob them of Fowler's talents until late November.
</P>
<P>
And that would also mean Fowler missing any potential Euro 2000
play-off game for his country - if Sweden beat Poland in 10 days
England would be scheduled to play in a two-legged game on
November 13 and 17. 
</P>
