<HEADLINE> Hingis Beats Mauresmo in Grand Slam Cup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, September 29 (Xinhua) -- World number one Martina Hingis
of Switzerland beat France's Amelie Mauresmo in her opening match
of the Grand Slam Cup to reach the semifinals of the world's
richest tournament in Munich on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Hingis overcame a sluggish start and confidently won a first-
set tiebreaker to record a 7-6 (7-1) 6-2 victory.
</P>
<P>
