<HEADLINE> Manchester United Beat Olympique Marseille 2-1 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, September 29 (Xinhua) -- Defending champions Manchester
United of England defeated Olympique Marseille of France 2-1 with
late goals from Andy Cole and Paul Scholes in a Group D Champions
League match on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Cole hit a spectacular overhead kick in the 77th minute after
Jaap Stam headed down a David Beckham free-kick and Scholes
scrambled home the winner for the English league leaders with
eight minutes left.
</P>
<P>
United defender Henning Berg had earlier earned the wrath of
his team-mates by getting caught in possession by Ibrahima
Bakayoko. He ran through on goal and hit a shot that came off the
body of Raimond Van Der Gouw and flew into the net after 41
minutes.
</P>
<P>
United were again below par and wasted the few chances they
created in the first period with Andy Cole missing several
opportunities. 
</P>
</TEXT>
