<HEADLINE> Romania, Hungary Are Factors of Stabilization in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, September 29 (Xinhua) -- Romania and Hungary were
factors of stabilization in south-eastern Europe, with ripple
effects on the entire zone, the visiting Hungarian Defence
Minister Szabo Janos Wednesday told a news conference after the
talks with his Romanian counterpart Victor Babiuc.
</P>
<P>
Referring to south-eastern Europe after the Kosovo conflict,
the Hungarian minister said the entire region must be supported
from the economic point of view, not necessarily in terms of
finance, but through investments in infrastructure.
</P>
<P>
Szabo Janos said the battalion called Romanian-Hungarian, will
become operational on December 31, 1999 and will be reviewed by
the defence ministers of the two states in April, next year.
</P>
<P>
The bilateral military relations are very good and can be a
positive signal for the political, economic and cultural relations
between Romania and Hungary, Victor Babiuc quoted Szabo Jabos as
saying. "The talks went in a friendly manner and I can affirm that
the Romanian-Hungarian military relations are excellent," Babiuc
stressed.
</P>
<P>
The Hungarian Defence Minister is officially visiting Romania
on September 29-30 at the invitation of his Romanian counterpart
Babiuc. 
</P>
</TEXT>
