<DOCNO> XIE19990930.0321 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-30 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Pinochet Would Never Kill Himself: Wife </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, September 29 (Xinhua) -- Former Chilean leader Augusto
Pinochet's wife on Wednesday said the retired general would never
consider suicide while battling extradition charges.
</P>
<P>
Lucia Pinochet said the 83-year-old general's health was
deteriorating and that he was very depressed because of the
long-running extradition case against him, but he would never kill
himself.
</P>
<P>
"The last thing a soldier would do is kill himself... For
someone to consider suicide he would first have to be in such a
painful state of depression that...my husband has not yet fallen,"
she said.
</P>
<P>
But she acknowledged that Pinochet was "very depressed."
</P>
<P>
"He is very, very depressed. After one year of
imprisonment,...given the pressure, his health is not good," she
told a press conference.
</P>
<P>
Pinochet, who ruled Chile with an iron fist for 17 years which
ended in 1990, is currently under house arrest in a hired mansion
in the south-west suburb of London.
</P>
<P>
He was arrested in a London hospital last October at the
request of a Spanish judge, who wants to try him on torture
charges dating from his rule.
</P>
<P>
Lucia Pinochet said her husband's extradition hearing was
politically motivated.
</P>
<P>
Earlier, in the hearing held at Bow Street Magistrates' Court
in central London, lawyers seeking Pinochet's extradition to Spain
said he actively encouraged torture during his rule.
</P>
<P>
But Pinochet's lawyer concluded their case by saying the
charges against the retired general do not amount to torture and
much of the conduct described in the charges even did not amount
to torture as defined in judgments of the European Court of Human
Rights.
</P>
<P>
The hearing, which openned on Monday and scheduled to last to
the end of this week, is to decide whether the charges against
Pinochet are extraditable. A decision is expected some time next
month. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
