<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chile to File Suit Against Spain </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTIAGO, September 29 (Xinhua) -- Chilean government is to
file suit against Spain before the international tribunal of The
Hague over the Pinochet case in December, Foreign Minister Juan
Gabriel Valdes reaffirmed on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Chilean Foreign Ministry communicated this decision in a formal
manner to the Spanish Foreign Ministry, during a meeting in
Madrid.
</P>
<P>
The judicial process will be done by Chileans and no foreigners
or Spanish judge can settle the problems of Chile, said Valdes.
</P>
<P>
Spanish Foreign Minister Abel Matutes told the press on
Wednesday that the Tribunal of The Hague will oblige all involved
to respect a decision in the Pinochet case.
</P>
<P>
Relations between Spain and Chile became tense after the the
detention last October of Chile's ex-military chief Augusto
Pinochet in London, at the request of a Spanish judge. The Chilean
government claim that the Spanish courts do not not have the
jurisdiction to try Pinochet.
</P>
<P>
On September 27 the hearing for the extradition of Pinochet to
Spain began in London, where the Spanish judge, Baltazar Garzon is
waiting to try Pinochet for crimes against humanity, perpetrated
during his military regime from 1973 to 1990. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
